## Interviewer Reflection

**Most important thing learned:**
The "screenshot relay" — one team member acts as the human bridge from Teams into Discord by literally taking screenshots — is a coordination mechanism we have not named in any synthesis document yet. It is the same functional pattern as RM's "bridge person" role, but the artifact is different (screenshots vs verbal updates). Worth pulling into patterns analysis.

**What to do differently next time:**
Ask immediately whether the interviewee or one of their teammates is the "screenshotter" or "bridge" or "asker" — these roles keep appearing and they are the cleanest segmentation signal I have found.

